messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

```json
[
  {
    "path": "/request/register",
    "handler": "registerRequest",
    "implementation_present": true,
    "path_is_prefix": false,
    "path_from_literal": true,
    "path_from_convention": false,
    "is_restful": true,
    "is_test": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/request/accept/{id}",
    "handler": "acceptRequest",
    "implementation_present": true,
    "path_is_prefix": false,
    "path_from_literal": true,
    "path_from_convention": false,
    "is_restful": true,
    "is_test": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/request/reject/{printRequestID}",
    "handler": "rejectRequest",
    "implementation_present": true,
    "path_is_prefix": false,
    "path_from_literal": true,
    "path_from_convention": false,
    "is_restful": true,
    "is_test": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/requests/pending",
    "handler": "acceptRequest",
    "implementation_present": true,
    "path_is_prefix": false,
    "path_from_literal": true,
    "path_from_convention": false,
    "is_restful": true,
    "is_test": false
  }
]
```

**Explanation:**

The code defines a Spring Boot REST controller `RegisterRequestController`.  The `@RequestMapping` annotation is used to map HTTP requests to specific methods within the controller.  Each entry in the JSON array represents an API endpoint defined in this file.

*   **`/request/register`**: This endpoint handles POST requests to register a new print shop. The `registerRequest` method handles this request.
*   **`/request/accept/{id}`**: This endpoint handles POST requests to accept a print shop registration request, where `{id}` is a path variable representing the request ID. The `acceptRequest` method handles this request.
*   **`/request/reject/{printRequestID}`**: This endpoint handles POST requests to reject a print shop registration request, where `{printRequestID}` is a path variable representing the request ID. The `rejectRequest` method handles this request.
*   **`/requests/pending`**: This endpoint handles GET requests to retrieve a list of pending registration requests. The `acceptRequest` method handles this request.

All paths are extracted from literal strings within the `@RequestMapping` annotations. All handlers are methods within the `RegisterRequestController` class, so `implementation_present` is true for all entries. All entries are RESTful APIs. None of the entries are marked as test APIs.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
path.title: Path

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.description: Whether the path string is a prefix rather than a full path.
path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention

is_restful_api.description: Whether the API entry is for a RESTful API, rather than other types of APIs.
is_restful_api.title: Is Restful Api

is_testing_purposes.description: Whether the API entry is intended for testing purposes, such as unit tests or functional tests.
